{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5e6e45d2-d8d7-4ceb-a743-8c49231d0ea2","content":"For NativeAOT, `createdump` isn't bundled, so you must point the runtime to it via `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`. Here are the pod spec changes:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  # Give time for dump writing before SIGKILL\n  terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 120\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      env:\n        # Enable automatic crash dumps\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        # 4 = Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage)\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        # Path to createdump (required for NativeAOT)\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n        # Dump output path (%e=exe, %p=pid, %t=timestamp)\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 4Gi\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — critical for NativeAOT since the runtime doesn't ship `createdump` itself\n- **`sizeLimit`** — adjust based on your app's memory footprint; full dumps can be large\n- **`emptyDir`** is ephemeral — if you need dumps to survive pod restarts, swap to a `PersistentVolumeClaim` or add a sidecar that uploads dumps to blob storage\n- Use `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=2` (Heap) instead of `4` (Full) to reduce dump size while still capturing managed state","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a48dd30-1aad-4776-b5b6-d4c33ece44f5","outputTokens":488,"requestId":"7640:E52A2:198C939:1D1AF3F:69FE9227"},"id":"71a9c5d3-b1fd-4275-bf0c-84de0d2c16be","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:47:29.348Z","parentId":"9b8f5025-ac4b-4897-8235-1bae0d0da459"}
